OL,3,CHow 300 bathtubs of concrete are
OL,4,Cending up in Thames Water sewers every
OL,5,Cyear
OL,7,FThe equivalent of 300 bathtubs of
OL,8,Fconcrete are ending up in sewers each
OL,9,Fyear because construction companies
OL,10,Fare not disposing of building waste
OL,11,Fproperly.
OL,13,FThames Water said firms needed to take
OL,14,Fmore responsibility and crack down on
OL,15,Fillegal waste which costs an estimated
OL,16,F#1.6 million to remove from the
OL,17,Fnetwork.
OL,19,FSpecial teams are using ultra-high-
OL,20,Fpressure jets to break it down before
OL,21,Fthe concrete can be sucked out.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G1/4
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
